==English==
===Etymology===
From ''[[beg]]'' + ''[[-ar]]''

===Noun===
'''beggar'''
#A person who [[beg|begs]].
#A person suffering from extreme [[poverty]].

====Translations====
*Dutch: [[bedelaar]].  As "Beggar" it is also used for "Geus" and as "Sea Beggar" for "Watergeus" (see translation in French for etymology)
*Norwegian: [[tigger]] ''m''
*French: [[mendiant]] ''m'' , [[gueux]] ''m''
*[[Greek]]: [[ζητιάνα]] ''f''
*Telugu: [[బిచ్చగాడు]] (bichchagaaDu) {{m}}, [[బిచ్చగత్తె]] (bichchagatte) {{f}}

====Derived terms====
*[[beggarly]]
*[[beggarliness]]
*[[beggary]]

===Verb===
'''beggar'''
#Make a beggar of someone; [[impoverish]].
#[[Exhaust]] the resources of.

